    /* Yoba, I wish I could stand out in the open fields here all day. All of the blooming flowers and weeds make such good medicine.
    peaking of, you wouldn't happen to have any taraxacum officinale - err, dandelions on you, would you? Their roots are a great liver tonic, and make for a good coffee substitute.

    Oh, you're looking rather flush today, I assume from your work? If not, you should schedule an appointment ASAP.

    Have you decided on a date for your yearly appointment yet, @?#$b#I'd like to get you scheduled in for that checkup we discussed when you first came down...

    You should really be careful on that farm, petname. I wouldn't want you to overwork yourself and end up in one of my beds. ...What? 'Petname?' Oh, @. If you're having trouble hearing, you should book an appointment with the clinic.

    %Harvey bumps into you.#$b#Oh my yoba, so sorry about that, @! Oh, you got a bruise there... Was that because of me? Or because of your farmwork? 
    Well, no matter... Here, take some of this with food and that should go away quickly... [351] **muscle remedy

    %You overhear harvey mumbling a few names of medications to himself. Hm? Oh, sorry, I'm just listing all of my patient's medications again so I don't forget... Say you aren't taking any outside of the ones I've given you, are you?

    ...$l#$b#Hm? I was staring? Oh, no, @. I was checking on that mark on your neck. You've still yet to make an appointment for that, by the way." 

    Oh, hey. I was looking over some of the medical records your last doctor sent over. Looks like you're chronically vitamin me deficient...
    Sorry, was that too cheesy?

    %Harvey yawns, his age peeking through as you notice the bags under his eyes. Sorry, I was up all last night taking inventory of our medicine reserves. Did you need something?

    Make sure you wear something warm while you're outside. I know summer's right around the corner, but it's still flu season! I wouldn't want you getting sick so early in the year, yeah?

    Question abt "Hey, I saw you exit the mines earlier, you didn't get hurt, right?_No.%Harvey presses a finger into a wound on your side. Liar. %His finger presses deeper in your wound, causing you to flinch. Do I need to remind you of what you promised me about getting my--err, your body hurt like this?_Well..._...$a#$b#Come to the clinic, let me patch you up properly...$a

    Is the pollen here bothering you at all? Sam's allergies hit him like a truck every year, and with you being new and all, I wouldn't be surprised if you also got a bit...
    Well, if you need any benadryl just let me know, yeah?

    Springtime's always my favorite, means there's always an excuse to stand outside and breathe fresh air. 
    That and I notice a few of my patients' moods improve this time of year. It really is a miracle season.

    %You notice Harvey running his fingers through his hair, clearly stressed. 
    Not now, @. I have a lot of work to finish. 
    ... Actually, I wouldn't mind your company. Maybe I could bounce a few ideas off of you.
    Do you know anything about Polyarthralgia?

    Huh, today's weather seems perfect for a plane ride.
    Speaking of, have you ever considered getting an AT-502 for your farm? I bet it'd make pest control a hell of a lot easier.
    */

